# Force LF line endings for all text files.
#
# Harness-rendered and composed files are produced with LF endings. On Windows,
# git's core.autocrlf=true would otherwise convert LF -> CRLF on checkout,
# causing `harness sync --mode=check` to report false drift (working tree vs the
# LF-normalized templating output). Forcing LF keeps the working-tree state
# consistent cross-platform and silences first-commit CRLF round-trip warnings.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit binary types — never normalized.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
*.gz binary
*.tar binary
